<br>
Went to Velk's for the second time since the change last night.  The first time was the night after the change, and I wrote that lunacy off to what goes on after any patch change to a zone.  But last night, I was right back at Orc 2, watching ubers simply stroll through and appropriate the spawns because they could, ignoring the group (mine) that had been there camping the area for a good hour.  <br>
<br>
Yes, part of the problem is that the front part of the zone (the spider ramps) facilitates this behavior.  But is this really the sort of behavior I can expect to deal with from people in their 50's?  <br>
<br>
I once thought that the greatest reward to be had for leveling up from the madding crowd in the Lake of Ill Manners was that people actually seemed to be getting nicer and more social.  Velk's, however, has truly changed my mind on this.  All it takes is a situation where you can get more if you are willing to be pushy and greedy, and people go right back to Orc 2.<br>
<br>
